<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
  English strings for the Pawn Diary mod. These are the DEFAULT language values; a translator
  can localize the whole mod (UI *and* the text fed to the LLM) by copying this file under
  Languages/<Language>/Keyed/ and translating the values - no code changes needed.

  Two deliberate exceptions are kept in English as a stable machine "schema" and are NOT keyed:
    - The structured prompt field labels (event:, pov:, role:, with:, setting:, you=, mood=, ...)
      and the initiator/recipient role words, in DiaryPromptBuilder / DiaryContextBuilder.
    - The greyed-out "LLM debug" diagnostic block under each entry, and the LlmClient network
      error messages (the latter are built on background threads, where .Translate() is unsafe).
  Everything a player reads, and every natural-language word the model reads, lives here.

  Placeholders: {0}, {1}, ... are filled in by the code in order.
-->
